# Forge System OS — backend credentials (Supabase)
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the two values from your Supabase project
# (Dashboard → Settings → API). Expo automatically loads `.env` and inlines any
# EXPO_PUBLIC_* variable into the app at build time, so `expo start` and
# `eas build` both pick these up.
#
# The anon key is PUBLIC by design — Row-Level Security protects your data, not
# key secrecy. Never put the service-role key here.
#
# (Alternative: instead of a .env file you can paste the same two values into the
#  *_FALLBACK constants in src/config.ts. Use one method or the other.)

EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_REF.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
